title: Little web scraping project
jobs_text:
"Hi there :) 
I need a simple web scraper for the Opensea website, only need to fetch a few items in some collections. 
Only a few simple requirements: 
1.  Performance, need to be fast as possible no more than 1 minute. 
2. The collection is dynamically parameter, today it can be X, and tomorrow it will be Y. 
     So it needs to be passed from the outside and not hardcoded. 
3. Thethe Opensea search have some filtering option, i need only two of them  
    (sorting low to high is the default): `Buy now` and `under X price`. 
4. Need to fetch something about 50 -300 items only. 
5. Need to integrate with working nodeJs server. the final result should be items number  
    as list. For example : [237, 8712 , 10781 , 1214...... , 6712]. 
 
*Please take a look at the following link which represents an example for a random collection that i choose with the third described requirement: 
 
 [priceFilter][symbol]=ETH&search[priceFilter][max]=0.999&search[sortAscending]=true&search[sortBy]=PRICE&search[toggles][0]=BUY_NOW 
 
Please respond with an offer with price, time estimation, scraper performance estimation, and technologies. 
 
I have to mention that I`m actually an SW engineer so i know this area. 
 
Thank you."
